the worker was walking/climbing up a ladder at approximately8' height, lost his footing, and fell through the rung/step

Reported to have fallen off of an extension ladder while desending into 10' vault.  No witnesses to incident.  Injured worker was removed from vault by FDNY and transported to Elmhurst Hospital for further medical attention.
Worker while bending down to pick up his tools accidently bumped his eye on a column brace causing a minor cut to his right eye. As a precautionary measurement worker was sent to local hospital.

The person who the ambulance was called for is the taping foreman.  He just finished eating lunch when he started to experience chest pains and sweating. Starting generator for temp power. The generator pull cord and safety shroud was missing so employee utilized makeshift pull cord. When she did this the metal shifted and a piece cut her ear. The individual was allegedly not wearing any PPE (hard hat). Following this, the individual went to the hospital on her own, not in an ambulance.
While assembling form work, a worker was hit on the wrist by a form tie being installed by another worker above when it fell.
Worker was removing insulation when it came loose and cut his arm.
Worker cut finger with chop saw.
Person involved in incident was transporting sheet rock on spyder lift when it rolled on its side.
A carpenter was lifting a wooden form when he injured his back
Construction worker was cutting a 2x4 with an electric saw and cut his leg.
Local 79 laborer employed by Waldorf Demolition was removing ductwork. Section of ductwork rolled on his foot resulted in laceration of his left foot
The adapter cap popped off of the fire hydrant. and hit a worker in the leg.
Worker was installing facade brick from a mast climber. The master climber operator raised the platform and the injured workers foot got caught between the mast climber tie back and the platform

The employee was standing at the window on the SE corner of the 79th floor. He was on the phone requesting a coffee from a fellow employee and has a seizure. He fell to the ground. The person on the receiving end of the phone call heard a thump as well as the Turner laborer who was working outside of the door. When the medic arrived the employee was not coherent. The medic checked his vitals and how responsive he was and instructed someone to call 911. His fellow employee informed the medic that he has previously had a seizure. The employee works for the owner. The ambulance was called
Worker's glove got caught in drill.
Worker was walking , tripped and fell.
A worker was pushing a piece of cast iron sanitary pipe through the slab and while he was looking up, some dust/debris fell into his eye.
The construction worker was operating the concrete pump hose when it fail striking the worker in the ankle causing him to fall and become injured.
While climbing a ladder, pencil rod punctured right arm of the lather/carpenter on 3 rd floor. after the first aid treatment, he wanted get checked out at the ER and went to ER.

Mr. Rodriguez Beato Darlin was carrying tile in a rolling flat bed cart to be stored in the Cellar Medical Office being used as a material storage room. The cart tipped over and landed on his right foot. Stateside Construction immediately rushed to his aide and brought him into our management office where we applied ice packs on his right foot. Mr. Beato's right foot had minor swelling and was black and blue. Upon ice being applied and raising his foot for 2-hours in our management office, Mr. Beato was able walk to the train station and went home.

Elkin Chica, an Asbestos Handler reported that when he was exiting a man-lift, he slipped on plastic poly and injured his hamstring, he also showed us scratches on his back, he was transported to Brooklyn Hospital and released

Ironworker was installing metal decking on 41st floor. Footing was lost and he fell off of the leading edge. Properly worn PFAS prevented worker from hitting the floor below. He struck his chin during the fall.
WORKER CLAIMED HE GOT PAINT ON HIS LEFT EYELID. EYELID SWOLLEN. WENT TO DOCTOR AND RELEASED.

Construction worker Karen Elizabeth Suazo Eden, employed by Just Klean LLC, subcontractor, was receiving garbage bags as part of rubbish removal operation.  Fellow coworker throws garbage bag and bag strikes the right leg - shin/ankle area of Ms. Eden.  She immediatly stopped work and was taken by private vehicle to par care urgent care a block away on Park Avenue.
Worker tripped on a pipe while working.

The injured worker was removing couplings from a chilled water pipe (connected to the chiller) with another worker from his crew, in the cellar.  The injured worker was struck in the face by one end of a condensed water pipe (6' black pipe, connected to the chiller) and knocked over.
Worker was removing 1 1/4 EMT pipe from a wall when it struck him in the forehead and nose
Sidewalk being replaced was chopped up using small backhoe. Worker was loading demolished concrete sidewalk spalls  into wheelbarrow. Worker felt strain in back while lifting piece of concrete.

Employee Ivanildo Martins Carmo employed by Magellan Concrete Co. was working on the 2nd floor deck at the time of the incident. Ivanildo was wearing full fall-protection gear and a harness while closing a column on the exterior at a height of 8 feet when he lost his balance. Immediately the harness yo-yo caught him and avoided a fall but Ivanildo did sustain very minor injuries to his right rib, arm and elbow. Ivanildo presented these minor injuries to his supervisor fully conscious, walking and speaking clearly. As an extra precaution we sent Ivanildo to medical care and he returned to work.

Jose Figuereo of Componet Assembly System was working on the 14th floor finished bathroom.  He was up on the 3rd  step of a 6ft A-frame ladder when he fell landing on his left shoulder.  He walked off site with his foreman to the hospital.
A piece of rebar struck the worker in the face.
Worker fainted due to heat and received cut on his head. Went to hospital in ambulance and received 5 stitches. Was released same day.
The worker was cleaning plywood when it slipped from his grasp and he was cut on the wrist by a nail that was embedded in the wood.

Worker was 1 of a 4 man team installing windows in the SE corner of the 45th floor. The team was lifting a window wall panel into place on the East elevation.  All 4 workers were standing on the floor manually installing the wall panel. As the team was lifting the wall panel into place, a 10 ft section of 5" black pipe struck one of the workers on the head.
Worker stepped on unsecured plank resulting in fall to lower level.

Worker at Magellen, Dijalmo Neto was participating in a stripping operation at the request of Allisson Silva Lima (Magellan Foreman). Mr. Neto was stripping column on the North East side when he lost his footing. Mr. Neto was supported by his Fall-Arrest- Device and did not suffer a fall. He was suspended and helped to the ground by staff. Mr. Neto did lose consciousness. Joshua Jacobson (Promont Competent Person) called for emergency services.
Worker installing Sheetrock stepped off a (2'-4") Baker scaffold onto his right foot injuring it.

Laborer cleaning classroom. Picked up piece of metal wall stud to discard. Although wearing gloves - Metal cut right thumb. Worker went to Urgent Care , Received First -Aid ie:received antibiotic   cream and band - aid adhesive strip. Worker cleared to work .- No medication prescribed - No further care required- No lost Time.

Contractor carting out debris from the building to a garbage truck parked on 53rd Street. Contractor set up garden hose for dust control, that ran from the building across the sidewalk and along the curb line to the truck. Contractor also laid a rubber mat protection cover over the hose at the area that crossed sidewalk and also had orange safety cones set up to alert pedestrians. Pedestrian exited 53rd St subway station and tripped and fell over mat. She was assisted to her feet by building security & contractor performing carting.  She admitted she was not watching where she was going.
Worker lost his balance on a ladder and fell with the ladder.

Interior Renovation work was happening at building under Active DOB permits. The worker fell off the first floor to the basement as seen by other co-worker. He stepped on OSHA planks. He did not tied off by him self and fell from 1st floor to cellar level. We have asked several laborer on site and No one has any idea what activity he was trying to perform without any knowledge of other team member. Then On site person called FDNY for taking him to hospital and FDNY came on site as well DOB to investigate incident.  Last he was reported to us that he broke his wrist

Raul Placencio, was working on the 23rd floor pushing sheet rock on a A-frame. His body became pinned between the A Frame and the wall. Mr. Raul Placencio left in an ambulance to Brooklyn Hospital for emergency medical treatment.

Equipment operator lifting pipes, lifted two pipes above the height of the existing pipes installed in the ground, pipes rolled back over the stop of the fork lift and rolled into a section of the cab the operator was sitting.  Worker cut his finger but was sent to hospital for additional evaluation.   Worker was released from hospital and is returning to the project today.

Worker was carrying lightweight sheet metal ducts to Apartment 4U when he scraped the top of his hand against an installed stud at the door opening. The employee was not working with anyone at the time of the incident, and walkways were accessible free of all debris. Upon discussion with the employee it was confirmed that he did not slip, trip, or fall, and that he was wearing all required personal protective equipment. The employee notified site safety immediately after the incident and received medical attention from the on site medic, and was taken to urgent care by his supervisor.
Worker was using a tube cutter to cut a pipe when her glove and left index got caught.

General Contractors laborers were pulling a mini container up the ramp to empty and dispose of construction waste. The wheel of the mini container broke which caused the construction laborer to fall back due to the weight and landed on an adjacent container injuring his back on the right side.
A Neptune worker was cleaning copper pipe on a ladder on the 41st floor.
The injured worker accidently got paint in his eye while spraying paint in an apartment.
Worker was working at 15 Floor  West side of building , perform stone installation at building wall  , cut his left hand when using small  grinder .
Worker was using an electric power saw and slipped and cut his leg.

At around 2:30 PM there was a worker named Kevin Gonzales who fell off a 4 foot ladder while installing Sheetrock drywell, his foot was hurting him, he was conscious, coherent and alert. While it seemed like a minor injury ems was called as a percation and he was taken into the ambulance for examination.

Hemiunu construction was performing a concrete pour of the retaining wall when carpenter Rony Posas fell off top of the wall apporximnety 14' ft due to to concrete pump hose exploted and got hit with concrete. he was wearing proper fall arrest system , Rony was taken to the hospital. spoke to witness yoni maldonado which is in the hospital with him he is in good condition and will be sent home today

At Approximately 11:15am yesterday 8/12/2020  An elevator worker was installing trough, inside the shaft, off of his sky climber on the 43rd floor.  When he was drilling to secure the bottom of the trough it let loose and started to fall.  When the trough started to fall the one worker instinctively went to grab it with his right hand.  The metal trough cut through the workers glove and cut his right thumb.

MCE was running conduit in trench at 33rd street entrance. Before work, Trench Protection was unnailed and removed. During break the hole was covered back up with 3/4 inch plywood, but was forgotten to be nailed and secured. MCE worker was delivering gangbox throught 33rd street entrance. when gangbox was pushed over plywood, plywood slipped and workers ankle got stuck in 5 inch hole.

Mr. Melido Zapata, a full time concrete construction mechanic for RNC Industries, claims to have sustained an injury to his leg. Mr. Zapata was attempting to exit the job site at days and end and claims to have slipped in a puddle during a rain storm. Mr. Zapata was taken from the site by EMS.
Working on 7th floor under very hot and humid conditions. The employee went to plug a fan into an extension cord and was shocked

NOT INJURY. Illness for Diabetic Dehydration: At aprox 12PM Mr. Moacir W. De Freitas Melo from Company INC/International Concrete was working on OSP doing footing forms. A co-worker observed Mr. Moacir (a diabetic) and saw that he showed signs of dehydration and heat-exhausted. They alerted SST Mr. Mendel Hershkop immediate. Immediately 911 was called. EMS arrived on scene and took his sugar level and blood pressure while administering oxygen. . As safety precaution, he was taken by EMS to Methodist hospital under observation and in stable condition ready to resume work.

Worker stated they were installing a waler beam, and the waler beam shifted which caused a pinch point to their right pointer finger. Worker went on their own to emergency room for further care. DOB was notified via phone call and dispatch stated no further inspection was required.
Was rolling out a roll of waterproofing in the crawlspace of the building, when he was pulling on the roll his back began to hurt and had a hard time moving.

Employee was descending from an A-frame ladder. The EE slipped from the second to last step of the ladder. On his way down, the EE struck his left knee on the ladder and fell to the floor. An ambulance was called and transported the EE to nearby medical facility.

Charles Sarmiento was going down the stairs carrying an ice cooler and he slipped. His legs fell in between the ladder and he twisted (?) his ankle. Charles gave permission to be taken to the doctors in a car and not an ambulance.
Worker was using the A-frame to move sheet-rock. The sheet-rock on the A-frame fell on worker, when the A-frame got blocked by a piece of sheet-rock on the floor.

Worker was placing his aluminum platform over the 11fl service elevator shaft in order to perform his work.  After he placed the first platform he turned around to go get the next platform.  When he turned he slipped landing face down on the slab son his right side.   He complained of pain in his right side lower rib area.  An ambulance was called and he was transported to Beth Israel for further examination.

At approximately 6:30 AM, Employee was descending an 8 foot a frame ladder. The employee slipped from the 2nd to last wrung of the ladder and fell to the floor. The employee struck his left knee on the ladder on the way down. The employee stated that he could not put weight on his left leg. He was taken from the site by ambulance to nearby medical facility.

Injured worker was preparing his work area to continue welding elevator rail divider tubes within Elevator Shaft D on the 2nd Floor. While setting up in the area he claimed that he was struck by a piece of shaft protection plank that had broken and fell from the 6th Floor above. He stated that a portion of the plank grazed off his hard hat and struck his right shoulder area.

David Garza and his 2-man crew at building to mobilize work site and where moving the scaffold platform on the sidewalk bridge to make room next to the building wall.  His finger got caught between the platform and sidewalk bridge plank and the aluminum platform severed his left index finger tip.

Workers were doing facade remediation work on 617 west end ave, east elevation removing mortar with a hammer and chisel and hammer slipped out of workers hand.  Hammer fell down to roof protection and bounced off and stuck pedestrians arm, causing a slight abrasion.  first aid kit was brought out to treat pedestrian and ambulance was called.  Pedestrian called a relative and did not want to wait for ambulance to come.  ambulance showed up but did not write a report as pedestrian had already left the scene.
While the employee was working, employee suffered an epileptic seizure. The employee was not injured as a result of the seizure but was taken by ambulance to the hospital, treated and released.
Worker was struck in the head by a piece of wood that fell

A worker was using a podium to secure reshores with banding straps to the underside of the slab on the 15th floor. The worker lost her balance and the ladder tipped over causing her to fall to her back on to the concrete deck, landing on top of her Self Retracting Life Line.

Worker was found on the floor of the 2nd fl bathroom after lunch unresponsive. Site medic attended to individual and 911 was called.  Worker was taken to St Lukes hospital where he was later pronounced dead.  Cause of death is unknown at this time.

The construction site at 95 Grattan street, Brooklyn was shut down on 03/27/2020 complying to the lock down initiated due to the pandemic.  The site remained closed for over 5 months and only just reopened on 08/20/2020. The site became very dirty as it was closed and required cleaning. Therefore Super Cleaning who we have hired for cleaning purposes was requested to provide labors and cleaning services for the site. In order to try to clean the area between the Foundation wall in the front and the shoring the labor tried to go down and accidently slipped and fell down 7-8 feet below.

Worker was moving from one location to another spreading steel decking over framing when the incident occurred.  He was wearing his harness and hadn't yet clipped into the anchor point nearby.  Worker fell approximately 15' to concrete floor below.  Area of injury is to his leg and pelvis.  No other injuries have been reported.

At approximately 9:00 am. Structure Tech Worker Jose Inonan reported an injury after mixing concrete. As told by Structure Tech worker, Jose had stacked approximately 5 bags of grout on top of none another to use. As Jose grabbed the top bag of grout from the stack, the other bags fell over and hit Jose's leg. Jose expressed discomfort in his knee. The on site medic conducted an evaluation. The on site medic administered an ice pack for the knee as well as ibuprofen. Jose decided he wanted further evaluation of his knee and a Structure Tech employee escorted Jose off the site.
Worker was clearing concrete pump line when line clogged.  Worker was in the process of unclogging line when wet concrete was discharged from pump line.  Worker was splashed with wet concrete.

Worker was on baker scaffold in stairwell and baker scaffold gave way casing worker to land on steps below. Onsite medic called for an ambulance where worker was taken to Bellevue Hospital for further treatment.

William Romero from A&G concrete was working on concrete forms with harness. He unhooked his lanyard to move his work position, slipped and fell 6 to 8 feet on the sandy ground  and twisted his right leg ankle at 8:10 am. He was sent to local urgent care just for a check up.

Person was working on scaffolding deck. A piece of plank with #9 wire hit his right arm upper elbow. Scratch/Abrasion with minor bleeding was observed at the location of injury. Person was taken to the hospital in a FDNY Ambulance. The time of the incident took place near the end of the work shift around 2:15 p.m. The weather condition was high 78/68 with partly cloudy skies.
Worker went into a diabetic shock.  EMT was called to the site.  The worker was not injured.  When SSM called in the incident, DOB stated it was a medical emergency.

Willowfield worker was working on the first floor of the project, when he was discovered on the ground by field supervision. Worker alleges to have fallen from portable ladder approximately 3-4 feet. No visible signs of injury. As a precuation, EMS notfied and worker taken for evaluation. Please note, worker is not employed by GC; date of hire noted on form is date subcontractor employee started work on the project.

On the 5th floor, in a 14ft floor to ceiling area, electricians were asked by masons constructing a CMU wall from a 5' high pipe scaffold platform to install remaining 3/4" l/v conduit to the ceiling so the masons could finish their wall. The electrician used a cordless band saw to cut a 44" piece along the ceiling and lost control of the piece. It fell a total of 3ft, first deflecting off ductwork immediately below the conduit and hit an adjacent mason on his hard hat and side of his head.

Worker hit by vehicle while moving Barriers on Fulton St to allow Concrete Boom Truck inside Barriers. Flagmen present, Vehicle went around Flagmen and struck Victim
Worker was framing walls. He reached into a bucket to grab screws and a Hilti Strip Shot went off and punctured the tip of his left index finger.
The worker claims while small pieces of metal got into his eyes while grinding. The worker did not report incident until 11/22/2019.
The worker claims while scraping window lintels he overexerted himself and had soreness. The worker did not report incident until 11/22/2019.
Two workers were handling a steel piece when one of the workers loose control due to steel slipper from his protection glove and fells on his left foot.

Daniel Arira was working on the North side of the 13th floor platform at approx. 4.30PM. When he was stripping a section of concrete formwork his hand got caught in between the platform and the corner form, which caused a cut and some bruising/swelling. After a visit to the doctor it was confirmed that no bones were broken.

The worker has diabetes, a pre-exisiting medical condition, he forgot to take his insulin the night of 11/26. The morning of 11/27 he reported to the site medic at 9 am because he was not feeling well. Upon the medic's suggestion, an ambulance was called. The worker was conscious and coherent when he was taken off site in the ambulance to urgent care.

DURING SPRINKLER AIR PRESSURE TEST ONE OF COUPLING IN THE BASEMENT BURST OUT AND MULTIPLE MICRO METAL ELEMENTS HIT INTO PLUMBER FACE AREA AND LEFT FOREARM. HE WAS TAKEN TO HOSPITAL FOR CHECK BY HIS BOSS AND RELEASED THE SAME DAY. NO ADDITIONAL MEDICAL TREATMENT WAS ADVISED.
Individual was exiting the basement when he slipped and fell on the floor.
Worker was removing cables from a packer truck when he fell and injured his side.
An employee of JM3 Carpentry named Jose Gomez was taping on the 6th floor when he fell from his stilts.  Worker complained that he hurt his tailbone an ambulance was called.

Our demolition subcontractor Alba Services Inc was removing a portion of the 7th floor slab to make a new floor opening for future Stair A, during which one of the workers below on the 6th floor entered the controlled access zone to remove one of the full mini's and some of the loose plaster ceiling fell and struck Richard Garcia in the head/face. Richard was wearing a hardhat and safety glasses. Richard was taken to our site office where he was cleaned up with soap and water, and administered an icepack for the swelling on his face. He was then take to a nearby walkin clinic for a checkup.
Worker was grouting bathroom wall tile and while reaching up with the grout float to apply grout, a steel pencil rod from ceiling punctured the web of his hand in between his fingers.

Individual was installing ductwork into ceiling grid on an 8 foot ladder and he fell off the ladder at a height of roughly 6 feet landing on his back. He was checked out by the on site medic and an ambulance was called to transport him to NYU Langhone for further testing, etc.

Worker was moving a bag of mortar from pallet to mixer when he slipped and fell onto the floor. Worker was able to walk to hoist and walk from hoist to medics office where he received treatment but was sent out to urgent care for evaluation due to pain. Worker had X-ray and MRI completed that both came back negative and was given two days of rest until he was able to come back to work.

A woman has died after being struck by a car while crossing the a nearby street to the site in Downtown Brooklyn. The crash happened shortly before 9:30 a.m. Wednesday 12/4/2019 at the intersection of Pearl and Willoughby streets. The man behind the wheel of a SUV hit the woman as she was attempting to cross Pearl Street mid-block. The SUV then crashed through construction fencing, sidewalk shed and metal barriers with such force, it sent a fire hydrant flying across the busy pedestrian walkway between Adams and Jay Streets which is north to the jobsite.

LACEY HARRELL EMPLOYEE OF INTERNATIONAL CONCRETE/STRUCTURAL SUPREME INJURED MIDDLE FINGER ON R HAND AT 11:30AM WHILE PERFORMING WORK AS FOLLOWS. AT THE TIME OF INJURY LACEY WAS PUTTING METAL BRACE ON TOP OF 2 BY 4 AND SMASHED FINGER, TOOK OFF GLOVE AND SAW WAS BLEEDING, ASKED FOR HELP. IN THE FUTURE LACEY WILL BE MORE CAREFUL AND WORK SMART.  DID NOT REFUSE MEDICAL CARE AND WAS RELEASED FROM WORK TO SEEK MEDICAL ATTENTION. HE RETURNED THE NEXT DAY FOR WORK WITH A FINGER BRACE AND WAS SEEN BY DR. ALYSSA GOPMAN AS PER DOCTORS NOTE  AND WAS CLEARED FOR WORK.
The worker was struck on the leg by an A-frame that fell.
Security Guard was patrolling area and entered a controlled Access Zone, upon entering the area he stepped on a plank which hit his nose.

Nature of work - Taping ceiling Worker William Pena was on stilts while taping the ceiling on the 6th floor.  Area was clear of Debis and material, etc  at time of incident,  From my understanding he lost his  balance and fell to floor.

Worker was stripping and cleaning on concrete stripping floor, stacking metal formwork shores (jacks). The jack was laying on the floor. As he grabbed the lower end of the jack he placed his middle finger in the center hole of the jack's base plate. As he moved the jack to close within itself, his finger was caught between the upper portion of the jack closing on the inside lower portion base plate where his finger was.
SSM REPORTS CARPENTER FELL 3 FEET OFF OF A LADDER AND INJURED BACK AND HAND DUE TO A MALFUNCTIONING POWDER ACUATED NAIL GUN

Non work related illness, Simone Rogers went to medic at 9am because she did not feel well. Dizziness and shortness of breath. The medic let her rest until break was over. Simone attempted to go back to work but started to get chest pains so Medic called 911 at that point. Simone was taken to the hospital at 10:50am for further observations.
During demolition of a wall on the 6th floor, the wall callopsed on worker .
Construction worker was working on a metal deck being prepared for concrete pouring.  Construction worker was walking fell forward, braced his fall and in doing so cut his hand on a piece of rebar

At start of day worker was acting erratic and disoriented before work began. His foremen was instructed to have him removed from site. At that moment worker went into convulsions and stopped breathing and it was determined he had signs of possible overdose. Narcan was administered by trained professional and attended to by medic where he began to breath again. FDNY and ambulance arrived shortly after and took him to be treated for possible overdose at near by hospital. Worker was treated and released from hospital.

As an Electrician (Jose Velaso of MT Electric) was pulling a feed wire for elevator Automatic Transfer Switch, he was using a wrench and a piece of kindorff as a lever to pull the wire through conduit, the wrench slipped off the kindorff, and Jose fell to the floor because he was using his body weight to push the lever down. On the floor directly under him there was a bolt being used to stabilize the kindorff, which Jose fell, bottom first onto and he was cut in his Perineum (area between his scrotum and anus)
The worker lost his footing while walking down a scaffold stair tower
Worker was leaving the site via a ramp leading to the turnstile, slipped and twisted his knee.
The worker was lifting a section of the ceiling when he lost his grip and the section fell on his foot.

Worker fell from the 5th floor to the 4th floor, during removing existing wood joist. One peice of joist hit the support and caused a part of floor where the worker was standing on to come down. Worker landed on his feet and walked down to the First floor unscaved. Worked took a 15 min break and decided to go to the hospital to just get checked out to make sure he is okay.

Juan C. Arevalo presented cut/abrasion on shin under R knee while doing work on a safe harness. Juan slipped and bumped his shin into pile adjacent to 433 Dean Street. Juan was fully conscious, walking and speaking clearly when notifying the Site Manager. Site Manager performed First Aid, no serious injury, iced the knee to reduce swelling. Juan refused EMS care but as an extra precaution we sent Juan to medical care across the street Prominis. An hour or so later, Juan returned to the site that day with a doctors note saying he is taken care of and can return to work on 12/16/19.

Worker was repositioning lift when it tipped over and landed on neighboring building. Workers safely removed by FDNY and brought to Harlem hospital for treatment. One worker was treated and released returning to site. Other worker was treated and stayed over night, no further information is known at the time of report. Boom lift equipment was safely rigged off neighboring building under the guidance of DOB Cranes and Derricks. Equipment and site was secured as per DOB inspector 3037 suggestions.

on 12/18/19 at approx 8:50 AM, Mr. Yordan Lantigua was travelling down a staircase from the 1st floor to cellar with both hands occupied during his descent.  Mr. Lantigua's right hand was in his pocket and the left hand was grasping a bag of plumbing supply when a misstep occured at the landing section at the bottom of the staircase, resulting in a fall.  Mr. Lantigua was transported via ambulance to Brooklyn Methodist Hospital located at 506 6th Street, Brooklyn, NY, 11215.  Mr. Lantigua was treated and released the same day.

The injured party was climbing onto a Baker scaffold at about 4' high to install ceramic tile on a wall.  He lost his balance and struck the side of his face on a rolling gate, causing a laceration to his left ear.
Electrician carrying light fixtures allegedly slipped on ice at loading dock on site

The employee was in pain and could not provide and account of the injury. We were informed that he slipped on a patch of ice while exiting the lift. The employee was taken to Brookdale medical center for care.

The worker was using a chipping gun on concrete columns. The worker did not report any incidents or injuries until the next day. The worker then stated that he had numbness in his fingers on his right hand and wrist pain.

Worker took hold of  # 11 rebar with only 1 hand . He was part of a 4 man team 2 on top of the delivery trailer and himself and a co worker on the ground, He had been using 2 hands prior to his injury. The weight of the single re-bar was too much for him to safely handle and the bar drove his  right hand onto the trailer bed pinning his middle finger causing his injury.

Worker injured on site-slipped while pushing Rubbermaid  up ramp on 37 and hit his face and had a bloody nose and appeared semi coherent-was brought down to 3rd floor office with assistance-ambulance was called and taken to Bellevue Hospital-Called DOB and notified them.

At time and place of occurrence a worker was pushing a one coarse baker scaffold along a hallway. The baker scaffold got hung up on bx-cable which was suspended approximately 7 feet from the ground. The baker scaffold fell over and struck the worker, the worker initially refused medical attention, but the job Superintendent Danny requested she be checked by an off-site medical facility. The building department accident line was immediately called. The worker was treated and released and has been given an appointment to go back to the facility on Thursday December 26, 2019 for a reassessment

Worker was moving/placing rebar in foundation of the hotel building, when on of the rebars moved from its location and hit the worker on his lower back and ankle. Worker stated that his ankle was hurt and his back was hurting. He requested and ambulance for treatment, which 911 was called at the time.  Worker was taken to the hospital in the ambulance.

WORKER WAS USING ELECTRIC GRINDER  TO CUT THE BOTTOM FLANGE OF AN EXISTING BEAM WHEN THE GRINDER BLADE BROKE AND PITCH OUT OF THE WORKER HANDS AND HIT HIM IN THE STOMACH AND THEN CUT HIM IN HIS FACE .

Worker was using electric grinder to cut bottom flange of existing beam when the grinder blade broke. As a result of the blade breaking, the grinder kicked back and hit him in the face, cutting his face.
Worker claimed he was struck by a block by another worker in his right ankle

WORKER WAS INJURED DURING GROUT INSTALLATION. WORKER WAS INSTALLING GROUT IN FOUNDATION ROCK ANCHORS. GROUT WAS BEING PUMPED REMOTELY FROM OUTSIDE OF THE BUILDING. THE HOSE CONTAINING THE GROUT FAILED FOR AN UNKNOWN REASON AND CAUSED THE GROUT TO SPRAY ONTO THE WORKER. THE WORKER'S FACE WAS SPRAYED WITH GROUT CAUSING GROUT TO GO INTO THE WORKER'S EYE.
